  "tacticalAnalysis": {
    "SWE": {
      "summary": "Sweden's 3-4-1-2 shape proved devastating against Tunisia's defensive block. NORDFELDT's distribution launched quick transitions, while LINDELOF and HIEN's composed ball-playing from the back beat Tunisia's press. GYOKERES and ISAK combined relentlessly as a twin strike partnership, creating space for AYARI to burst through the lines. Wing-backs GUDMUNDSSON and BERNHARDSSON stretched the 5-man Tunisian defence effectively.",
      "strengths": [
        "Twin striker combination (GYOKERES + ISAK) stretched Tunisia's 5-back shape, creating overloads and channels for midfield runners",
        "Early goal from AYARI at 7' settled the match, forcing Tunisia to open up and play into Sweden's transition strengths",
        "High defensive line (54m in final third) allowed sustained attacking pressure and quick counter-press recovery after losing the ball",
        "Wing-backs BERNHARDSSON (9 ball progressions) and GUDMUNDSSON provided constant width, pinning Tunisia's wing-backs deep"
